removed.title: Eating Crow
removed.description: The gang enters the heart of the American Gothic South in order to help an attractive farmer who Fred wants to impress with his mystery-solving prowess. A horrifying Scarecrow has come to life and attempts to drive everyone off his farm.

removed.title: Mysteries on the Disorient Express
removed.description: Unhappy about a mystery free, three day, cross-country train trip with the gang, Fred is pleasantly surprised to discover a monster mystery on board. He's less pleasantly surprised when that mystery is interrupted by a second mystery, then a third, then a fourth…

removed.title: Trading Chases
removed.description: Fred switches places with Jeff, the tour guide at a history museum, to give him a chance to lead the gang in solving a mystery. The mystery: a frightening Egyptian crocodile deity is terrorizing the museum. The problem: Fred is instantly jealous of this new guy and sets out to solve the mystery before he can, using Jeff's tour group of children!

removed.title: The Norse Case Scenario
removed.description: The gang goes on a camping trip. Fred's desire for the gang to get in touch with their natural instincts and hones their mystery skills turns into on-the-job training as Viking Ghosts attack and attempt to drive them away or worse.

removed.title: Where There's a Will, There's a Wraith
removed.description: It's a classic haunted house caper when a rich man, whose life Scooby once saved, writes Scooby into his will!  Now, to collect his share of the fortune the gang must spend a night in a creepy mansion along with the rich man's kooky relatives and, worse, a spooky phantom!

removed.title: There Wolf
removed.description: The gang rushes Scooby to an animal hospital when he suddenly falls ill. Things go from bad to worse when they discover the Gothic, old hospital is also home to a rampaging werewolf.

removed.title: Screama Donna
removed.description: To solve the mystery of a ghostly performer haunting her former venue, the gang has to pretend to be a rock band themselves! But can they solve the case before Velma has to actually get on stage and sing?

removed.title: Ghost in the Mystery Machine
removed.description: Fred's worst nightmare comes true when an evil spirit possesses the Mystery Machine and turns his beloved van into an unrelenting monster out to destroy him and the gang before they can solve the mystery.

removed.title: I Scooby Dooby Do
removed.description: The gang is honored to take part in the wedding of two close friends. But can Best Man Shaggy and Maid of Honor Daphne save their friend's perfect day before it's ruined by a Ghost Bride bent on destroying everyone else's happily ever after?

removed.title: Scary Christmas
removed.description: It's Christmas Eve and Fred is ready to solve a Christmas mystery! Unfortunately the town the gang has arrived in is being attacked by a Pterodactyl and it doesn't seem to have anything to do with Christmas!

removed.title: Omelettes Are Forever
removed.description: The gang gets caught up in international espionage and intrigue when they cross paths with British secret agent, Jenny Vex, and must help her complete her dangerous mission of stopping a monstrous, evil mercenary called Minus from killing the meal of breakfast - forever.

removed.title: Greece Is the Word
removed.description: We travel back to Ancient Greece, where the gang plays unique roles in a Greek Mystery involving the mythological spider woman, Arachne, and her attempts to disrupt the royal wedding that would unite two great cities.

removed.title: Giant Problems
removed.description: Daphne brings the gang to Ireland to visit an ancient Blake family castle. As the gang becomes enchanted by the magical emerald isle, an angry, rampaging giant makes them reconsider just how wonderful all the old myths and legends really are.

removed.title: Scroogey Doo
removed.description: The Scooby Gang enter Dickens' classic "A Christmas Carol" as they try to get to the bottom of the mysterious ghost tormenting Scrooge in 1843 England. Unfortunately, the Ghosts of Christmas Past, Present and Yet To Come begin to convince Velma she's on a disastrous path of her own.

removed.title: Halloween
removed.description: In a strange town the gang tries to convince Fred he's mistaken in his firm belief that you can't solve a mystery on Halloween. When an evil witch appears and frightens the town into calling off Halloween, the gang learns this isn't Fred's first run-in with this witch and the true story behind Fred's feelings about Halloween.

removed.title: Be Quiet Scooby-Doo!
removed.description: To solve the mystery of a creepy crystal crawler, a bat-like cave monster, the gang must venture into the Crystal Canopy, a labyrinth of intricate crystal formations. To make things worse, they can't speak a word while in the Canopy because even the slightest sound will bring the crystals crashing down around them!

removed.title: Renn Scare
removed.description: The gang heads to Velma's beloved authentic Renaissance Faire, where they must find a way to infiltrate the royal feast in order to stop an evil court jester from ending the king's reign, permanently, and closing the faire.

removed.title: The Curse of Kaniaku
removed.description: On a trip to Japan to visit Velma's friend, the gang comes face to face with the ancient crab monster Kaniaku. They attempt to solve a 700 year-old mystery; meanwhile Daphne accidentally becomes a viral media sensation in Japan.

removed.title: Naughty or Ice
removed.description: Daphne brings the gang to a fancy Ice Hotel co-owned by her family where a new exhibit of ice age artifacts is opening. Things heat up, however, when a frozen Ice Man thaws out and goes on a rampage inside the hotel. Solving the mystery becomes even more complicated when the gang realizes Daphne may just have ulterior motives for going to the hotel to begin with.

removed.title: Professor Huh? Part 1
removed.description: Fred and the gang are called in to help with a mystery involving a figure from Fred's past, Professor Huh? The race to see which gang could solve the mystery first is on, as the rest of the gang learns there's more to this story than meets the eye and Fred's interest in finding Professor Huh? is as personal as it gets.

removed.title: Vote Velma
removed.description: When the ghost of a small town's founder returns to scare off mayoral candidates, the gang decides to run Velma as mayor to bait the ghost. They quickly discover however, that Velma lacks the skill set to make her a popular politician.

removed.title: Gremlin on a Plane
removed.description: The Gang has seats on the largest airplane ever to fly the open airways! Unfortunately the plane is also beset by a Gremlin bent on sabotaging the flight! The Gang has to step up to solve the airborne mystery as well as deal with something even scarier: Daphne flying a plane!

removed.title: Area 51 Adjacent
removed.description: Daphne always dreamed of meeting extra terrestrial life but that dream becomes a nightmare when the gang gets caught up in the mystery of a scary Alien Monster and brought to Area 53, a government facility so secret, it's two numbers higher than Area 51!

removed.title: The People vs. Fred Jones
removed.description: Fred is on trial, accused of being the real mastermind behind all the mysteries he's solved. With the help of his defense attorney, Daphne, we go back over the day's events in a town that had been abandoned since the 1950s because of a toxic chemical spill where a toxic mutant has been terrorizing all who dare go near the town.

removed.title: Night of the Upsetting Shorts
removed.description: The gang heads to Shaggy's beloved grandmother's Florida retirement home, where they learn a crazed Ape Man has been frightening the elderly residents. In order to lessen Shaggy's worry that he doesn't give his Grammy enough bragging rights, the gang pretends Shaggy is their leader and Daphne, his adoring girlfriend, inadvertently putting more pressure on Shaggy to solve the mystery of the Ape Man - who, as it turns out, is less horrifying than the shorts Fred decided to wear to beat the Florida heat.

removed.title: Pizza O'Possum's/The Curse of Half-Beard's Booty
removed.description: Pizza O'Possum's: Shaggy drags the gang to a childhood arcade where he's determined to finally collect enough tickets to win the prize he's wanted since he was a boy. Cutler explains that he's turned over a new leaf and opened up this restaurant to earn an honest living. Unfortunately, the ghost of a legendary pirate, Half-Beard, has been scaring away his customers. Fred and Cutler form an uneasy alliance as he joins the gang on a treasure hunt at Double-Cross Cove where Half-Beard's treasure is supposedly buried.

removed.title: Some Fred Time
removed.description: The gang force the over-worked Fred to relax and take time off from mysteries at Daphne's family's beach house. Unfortunately, when a walking shark attacks the ritzy beach community, the gang is forced to solve the mystery without Fred finding out about it.

removed.title: Protein Titans 2
removed.description: When a mega-successful video game company tries to buy an old algorithm from Velma and convince her to work for them in San Francisco, the gang becomes embroiled in the mystery of a video game villain who has seemingly come to life, the Ghost Chef.

removed.title: In Space
removed.description: A very bad parking choice on Fred's part leads the gang to an asteroid mining base in outer space where an alien virus appears to be infecting the crew one by one, turning them into evil skull-headed aliens. The paranoid, terrified gang must try to solve the mystery before the virus reaches them.

removed.title: Me, Myself and A.I.
removed.description: When an Artificial Intelligence takes over the building of a trendy tech company, the Gang has to solve the computerized mystery and maybe learn a lesson about relying too much on technology.

removed.title: Silver Scream
removed.description: The gang tours an old Hollywood Studio but they soon uncover a mystery concerning the ghost of a silent film comedy star who has returned to make sure his recently discovered final film is never seen.

removed.title: World of Witchcraft
removed.description: The gang goes to Salem, Massachusetts for a historical festival, only to discover history repeating itself as a demon has been set loose on the town, supposedly summoned by a witch as revenge for the infamous 17th Century Salem Witch Trials. As the Mayor stirs up fear and paranoia, the whole town goes witch hunt crazy and it's not long before suspicions fall on the gang, in particular, Daphne, who feels empathy for the eccentric, free spirited women accused of witchcraft 350 years ago.

removed.title: Be Cold, Scooby-Doo!
removed.description: The gang hits the ski slopes, although Daphne's more focused on nailing Fred with a revenge snowball. Their snowy fun is soon interrupted by the appearance of an evil Snowman Monster eager to scare all trespassers off his mountain.

removed.title: If You Can't Scooby-Doo the Time, Don't Scooby-Doo the Crime
removed.description: Fred is excited to visit the Vault, a high security prison no convict has ever escaped from. But when the ghost of Stealing Stan, an inmate who always claimed to be innocent, terrorizes the prison, Fred has to solve the mystery and rethink his stance on criminal justice!

removed.title: Saga of the Swamp Beast
removed.description: The gang's trip to the bayou is ruined by a shambling Swamp Beast that's scaring away anyone who dares to enter its soggy domain!
